<div class="container">
    <h1>7. Child Selectors</h1>

    <p>Child selectors allow you to target elements that are nested within other elements, referred to as children of their parent element. There are two primary ways to do this: <strong>descendant selectors</strong> and <strong>direct child selectors</strong>.</p>

    <h2>3.1 Descendant Selector</h2>
    <p>The descendant selector matches all elements that fall within a specified ancestor element, regardless of depth. This selector is created simply by spacing elements in the CSS rule.</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            article h2 { color: #333; font-size: 20px; }
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            &lt;h2&gt;Not selected&lt;/h2&gt;<br>
            &lt;article&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;h2&gt;This heading will be selected&lt;/h2&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;h2&gt;This heading will be selected&lt;/h2&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;<br>
            &lt;/article&gt;
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>3.2 Direct Child Selector</h2>
    <p>The direct child selector only targets elements that are immediate children of a parent element. This is done by using the greater than <code>&gt;</code> symbol between parent and child selectors.</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            article &gt; p { color: #333; font-size: 16px; }
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            &lt;p&gt;Not selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &lt;article&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;This paragraph will be selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;Not selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;<br>
            &lt;/article&gt;
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>3.2.1 Child Selectors Overview</h2>
    <table class="selector-table">
        <thead>
            <tr>
